<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
    <head>
        <title>LabMate - About</title>
        <link rel="icon" type="image/x-icon" href="/img/favicon.ico">
        
        <meta charset="UTF-8">
        <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">

        <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/theme-style.css">
        <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/navbar-style.css">

        <style>
            body::before{
                content: "";
                position: fixed;
                width: 100%;
                height: 100%;
                background-size: cover;
                background-position: center;
                background-repeat: no-repeat;
                background-image: url("/img/bg-image1.jpg");
                opacity: 0.05;
                z-index: -1;
            }

            body{
                background: var(--green);
                margin: 0;
                padding: 0;
                overflow-y: scroll;
            }

            .frame {
                position: relative;
                display: flex;
                flex-direction: column;
                align-items: center;
                max-width: 1920px;
                max-height: 1080px;
                padding: 40px 20px;
            }

            .frame h1 {
                position: relative;
                text-align: center;
                font-weight: 600;
                font-size: 50px;
                padding: 40px 0;
            }

            .section {
                position: relative;
                width: 900px;
                background: var(--off-white);
                border-radius: 15px;
                padding: 30px;
                margin: 20px 0;
                backdrop-filter: blur(10px);
            }

            .section h2 {
                font-size: 24px;
                margin-bottom: 20px;
            }

            .section p {
                font-size: 18px;
                line-height: 1.6;
                margin-bottom: 15px;
            }

            .libraries {
                display: grid;
                grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(200px, 1fr));
                gap: 15px;
                margin-top: 20px;
            }

            .library-item {
                background: var(--dark-blue);
                padding: 15px;
                border-radius: 10px;
                color: var(--off-white);
                transition: all 0.3s ease;
                cursor: pointer;
                position: relative;
                overflow: hidden;
                height: 25px;
            }

            .library-item:hover {
                height: auto;
                min-height: 120px;
                background: var(--dark-blue);
                color: var(--off-white);
                transform: translateY(-5px);
                box-shadow: var(--dark-blue);
            }

            .library-description {
                font-size: 14px;
                line-height: 1.4;
                opacity: 0;
                transform: translateY(20px);
                transition: all 0.3s ease;
                background: var(--dark-blue);
                color: var(--off-white);
            }

            .library-item:hover .library-description {
                opacity: 1;
                transform: translateY(0);
            }

            .team {
                display: grid;
                grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(250px, 1fr));
                gap: 20px;
                margin-top: 20px;
            }

            #members {
                font-size: 18px;
                line-height: 1.4;
            }
        </style>
    </head>
    <body>
        {{> navbar-signedout}}

        <div class="frame">
            <h1>About LabMate</h1>
            
            <div class="section">
                <h2>Lab Reservation System</h2>
                <p>Labmate is a web application for managing real-time laboratory seat reservations in De La Salle University. Students and faculty (lab technicians) can reserve seats in available timeslots and block slots for walk-in reservations, respectively.</p>
                <p>This is a major course output in fulfillment of the academic requirement for CCAPDEV for Term 2, AY 2024-2025.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="section">
                <h2>NPM Libraries Used</h2>
                <div class="libraries">
                    <div class="library-item">
                        <div class="library-name">express</div>
                        <div class="library-description">Web app framework used to build our server and handle backend (routes, requests, responses, middleware, etc.).</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="library-item">
                        <div class="library-name">mongoose</div>
                        <div class="library-description">Library used to connect to MongoDB and manage database interactions.</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="library-item">
                        <div class="library-name">express-session</div>
                        <div class="library-description">Session middleware for express, used to manage user sessions and authentication.</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="library-item">
                        <div class="library-name">connect-mongodb-session</div>
                        <div class="library-description">Library used to store session data in MongoDB so that sessions persist even after server restarts.</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="library-item">
                        <div class="library-name">argon2</div>
                        <div class="library-description">Primary hashing library to hash user passwords when stored in the database.</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="library-item">
                        <div class="library-name">express-fileupload</div>
                        <div class="library-description">Middleware used to handle file uploads for when users upload a new profile picture.</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="library-item">
                        <div class="library-name">cookie-parser</div>
                        <div class="library-description">Used to parse cookies and handle the session cookies.</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="library-item">
                        <div class="library-name">express-handlebars</div>
                        <div class="library-description">Used to allow dynamic and reusable HTML templates.</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="library-item">
                        <div class="library-name">path</div>
                        <div class="library-description">Used to handle file paths.</div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="section" id="members">
                <h2>Developed By</h2>
                <div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-around; margin-bottom: 20px;">
                    <div><strong>Mary Grace Capote</strong></div>
                    <div><strong>Anja Gonzales</strong></div>
                    <div><strong>Denise Liana Ho</strong></div>
                    <div><strong>Angelo Rocha</strong></div>
                </div>
                <p style="text-align: center; margin-bottom: 20px;"><strong>CCAPDEV S16 - Group 11</strong></p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </body>
</html>
